text: Katarína Neveďalová (born 10 November 1982) is a Slovak politician. Between 2009 and 2014 she was a Member of the European Parliament, where she was a member of the Progressive Alliance of Socialists and Democrats (S&D;). She became Vice-President of the Party of European Socialists in 2012. ==References== Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:People from Nitra Category:Direction – Social Democracy MEPs Category:Women MEPs for Slovakia Category:MEPs for Slovakia 2009–2014
